"""
Data Source
-----------
This study utilized questionnaire data from the Chinese General Social Survey (CGSS) dataset.

About CGSS:
-----------
The Chinese General Social Survey (CGSS), initiated in 2003, is China’s earliest nationwide, 
comprehensive, and continuous academic survey project. In 2003, the Department of Sociology 
at Renmin University of China collaborated with the Survey Research Center of the Hong Kong 
University of Science and Technology to design and launch the first CGSS and its first phase, 
drawing on international experience and their own expertise. Since 2010, the second phase of 
CGSS has been hosted by the National Survey Research Center at Renmin University of China.

Data Access:
------------
In accordance with the CGSS charter, annual data are released on the CGSS official website 
(http://cgss.ruc.edu.cn/) and the China National Survey Data Archive (CNSDA) website 
(http://www.cnsda.org/index.php) two years after survey completion. Currently, the database 
includes data from the following years: 2003, 2006, 2008, 2010–2013, 2015, 2017, 2018, and 2021.

Note:
-----
Users should cite the CGSS in any publications using these data and comply with 
the dataset’s usage agreements.
"""
